### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Please consider providing multiple `ErrorHandler`. The `ErrorHandler` is a regular provider but many use cases require multiple error handlers:

```typescript
class ErrorHandlerA implements ErrorHandler {}

class ErrorHandlerB implements ErrorHandler {}

@NgModule({
  providers: [
    { provide: ErrorHandler, useClass: ErrorHandlerA, multi: true },
    { provide: ErrorHandler, useClass: ErrorHandlerB, multi: true },
  ] 
})
```

**Example problem:** an application is going to use several logging libraries - A and B.

**Example solution 1:** implements a `CustomErrorHandler` and manually integrates both loggers.
```typescript
class CustomErrorHandler implements ErrorHandler {
  constructor(
    private loggerA: LoggerA,
    private loggerB: LoggerB
  ) {}

  handleError(error: any): void {
    this.loggerA.error(error);
    this.loggerB.error(error);
  }
}
```

**Example solution 2:** introduces a `MultiErrorHandler`: "reimplements" the `ErrorHandler` as a multi provider: 
```typescript
@Injectable()
export class MultiErrorHandler implements ErrorHandler {
  constructor(
    @Optional()
    @Inject(MultiErrorHandler)
    private handlers: ErrorHandler[] | null
  ) {}

  handleError(error: any): void {
    this.handlers?.forEach((handler) => handler.handleError(error));
  }
}

class LoggerAErrorHandler implements ErrorHandler {
  constructor(private loggerA: LoggerA) {}
  
  handleError(error: any): void {
    this.loggerA.error(error);
  }
}

class LoggerBErrorHandler implements ErrorHandler {
  constructor(private loggerB: LoggerB) {}
  
  handleError(error: any): void {
    this.loggerB.error(error);
  }
}

@NgModule({
  providers: [
    { provide: ErrorHandler, useClass: MultiErrorHandler },
    { provide: MultiErrorHandler, useClass: LoggerAErrorHandler, multi: true },
    { provide: MultiErrorHandler, useClass: LoggerBErrorHandler, multi: true },
  ] 
})
```


### Proposed solution

Consider the `ErrorHandler` as a multi provider:

```typescript
@NgModule({
  providers: [
    { provide: ErrorHandler, useClass: ErrorHandlerA, multi: true },
    { provide: ErrorHandler, useClass: ErrorHandlerB, multi: true },
    ...
  ] 
})
```

